Java-8 introduced the modern, [`java.time` Date-Time API](https://www.oracle.com/technical-resources/articles/java/jf14-Date-Time.html) which supplanted the outdated and error-prone legacy `java.util` Date-Time API. Since then it has been highly recommended to switch to the modern API.

