The responsible feature is USE_GETTERS_AS_SETTERS which is turned on by default: https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-databind/wiki/Mapper-Features

As of Jackson 2.9, it looks like null-handling for specific properties can be configured with [`@JsonSetter`][1], for example:

    @JsonSetter(nulls = Nulls.AS_EMPTY)
    public void setStrings(List&lt;String&gt; strings) {
        this.strings = strings;
